Connect the side that pulls in water to the tube that's connected to your garden hose. Open the hand valve completely. On the outside of your house, open the garden hose spigot to find the right water flow volume. Plug in the fan and turn it on. When you're ready to switch off your homemade air conditioner, close the hand valve and unplug your fan.
